            <note>
                <para>The DTRL_Enable parameter is accessible only to Dealers.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">WIRING INFORMATION:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>None required.</para>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <title>LOWW</title>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn on wipers (to the low speed) with IGN switch in run position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that the low beam headlights (and tail, marker and clearance lights) are on.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn on wipers (intermittent) with IGN in Run position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify low beam headlights are on.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn off wipers and verify headlights remain on.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cycle the Headlight switch and verify that headlights are off.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <title>DTRL</title>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Set the IGN switch to run with the park brake off.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Verify that low beam headlights are on.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Set the park brake to on and verify that the low beam headlights turn off.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Set the IGN switch to accessory with the park brake off and verify that the low beam headlights
                    are off.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">HOW TO ADD THIS FEATURE:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <title>LOWW</title>
        </para>
        <para>(1)&#9;Activate the LOWW_Enabled parameter using the Diamond Logic&#174; Builder software, or see a
            dealer.
        </para>
        <para>
            <title>DTRL</title>
        </para>
        <para>(1)&#9;Go to your local dealer and have them enable the DTRL_Enabled parameter with their version of the
            Diamond Logic&#174; Builder software.
        </para>
